a","description":"King John of England agreed to a charter of rights called the Magna Carta. The document was originally drafted by the Archbishop of Canterbury to establish peace between King John and a group of rebel barons. The Magna Carta was completed in 1215 and is now considered to be one of the greatest constitutional documents of all time.","url":"https://www.nationalarchives.gov.uk/education/medieval/magna-carta/","urlTitle":"National Archives - Magna Carta","jurisdictionLevel":1},{"id":1705188,"age":70,"year":"1224","julianDay":2168117,"title":"France Declares War on England","description":"France declared war on England as Louis VIII of France attacked Poitou and northern Gascony.","jurisdictionLevel":1},{"id":1705189,"age":105,"year":"1259","julianDay":2180901,"title":"100 Years of Conflict Between England and France Ends","description":"Treaty of Paris was signed on December 4, 1259, which ended 100 years of conflict between England and France.","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Treaty_of_Paris_(1259)","urlTitle":"Wikipedia - Treaty of Paris 1259","jurisdictionLevel":1}],"lifeSummary":"Alice Farendon was born in 1154, in Lancashire, England. She married William De Farrington in 1189, in Farington, Lancashire, England. They were the parents of at least 1 son."},"et":{"1154–":"1154–Surnud","1121–Male":"1121–Surnud","1190–1245":"1190–1245","1154–Female":"1154–Surnud","1190":"1190","1259":"1259","1215":"1215","1224":"1224","1245":"1245","1189":"1189","1154":"1154","1121":"1121","Farington, Lancashire, England":"Farington, Lancashire, England","Lancashire, England":"Lancashire, England"},"fi":{"1154–":"1154–Kuollut","1121–Male":"1121–Kuollut","1190–1245":"1190–1245","1154–Female":"1154–Kuollut","1190":"1190","1259":"1259","1215":"1215","1224":"1224","1245":"1245","1189":"1189","1154":"1154","1121":"1121","Farington, Lancashire, England":"Farington, Lancashire, England","Lancashire, England":"Lancashire, England"},"fr":{"1154–":"1154–Décédée","1121–Male":